Definition: the position of greatest importance or advancement
Example: the leading position in any movement or field; the Cotswolds were once at the forefront of woollen manufacturing in England; the idea of motion was always to the forefront of his mind and central to his philosophy
Synonyms: forefront, cutting_edge, position, the, of, greatest, importance, or, advancement, leading, in, any, movement, field, Cotswolds, were, once, at, woollen, manufacturing, England, idea, motion, was, always, to, his, mind, and, central, philosophy
Category: noun.cognition
